\begin_layout Standard
Given that 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{i\mathbf{k}}$
\end_inset

 is a complex numnber then we will optimize in the real and complex parts
 of this element, this can be seen in the following reasoning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using the chain rule on the function 
\begin_inset Formula ${\rm {\rm \text{Tr}}}\left(e^{-\beta\overline{H_{\bar{S}}}\left(t\right)}\right)=A\left(\varepsilon\left(t\right),\eta\left(t\right)\right)$
